// Shared source side for the TDS-output persistence EMIT tests: the input class,
// an empty mapping, and the trivial service whose output is ingested. Each test
// pairs this with its own db.pure (the relational target table, whose columns are
// dictated by the persistence config). Referenced via an inline root+files
// dependency and intentionally has no *.emit.yaml descriptor, so discovery never
// runs it as a test of its own.

###Pure
Class test::Person
{
  name: String[1];
}

###Mapping
Mapping test::Mapping ()

###Service
Service test::Service
{
  pattern : 'test';
  documentation : 'test';
  autoActivateUpdates: true;
  execution: Single
  {
    query: src: test::Person[1]|$src.name;
    mapping: test::Mapping;
    runtime:
    #{
      connections: [];
    }#;
  }
  test: Single
  {
    data: 'test';
    asserts: [];
  }
}
